.SH 3 "Theo de Raadt hates the Plan 9 license (circa 2003)"
.PP
In the year 2002, the fourth edition of Plan 9 was released under the
Lucent Public License\&.\c
.NS
http://git.9front.org/plan9front/plan9front/HEAD/lib/legal/lpl/f.html
.NE
This time, Theo de Raadt was not impressed:
.FS
.QS
.PP
The new license is utterly unacceptable for use in a BSD project\&.
.PP
Actually, I am astounded that the OSI would declare such a license
acceptable\&.
.PP
That is not a license which makes it free\&. It is a \fIcontract\fP with
consequences; let me be clear \(em it is a contract with
consequences that I am unwilling to accept\&.
.QE
.FE
.PP
